# Enforce LF line endings for all text files Git tracks.
#
# Without this, Windows contributors with `core.autocrlf=true` end up with
# CRLF blobs in some commits and LF blobs in others (whatever was on disk
# when committed). The lefthook sync-skills check compares the synced
# output against `.claude/skills/` and `plugin/skills/` byte-for-byte;
# any line-ending drift breaks the check and produces false-positive
# "out of sync" reports.
#
# `text eol=lf` instructs Git to:
#   - Normalize line endings to LF in the stored blob (regardless of OS)
#   - Check files out as LF in the working tree (overrides `core.autocrlf`)
#
# After adding this file, run `git add --renormalize .` to renormalize
# any blobs already stored with CRLF.

*               text=auto
*.md            text eol=lf
*.json          text eol=lf
*.yml           text eol=lf
*.yaml          text eol=lf
*.sh            text eol=lf
*.ts            text eol=lf
*.tsx           text eol=lf
*.js            text eol=lf
*.mjs           text eol=lf
*.cjs           text eol=lf
*.html          text eol=lf
*.scss          text eol=lf
*.css           text eol=lf

# Binary — never normalize
*.png           binary
*.jpg           binary
*.jpeg          binary
*.gif           binary
*.svg           text eol=lf
*.ico           binary
*.woff          binary
*.woff2         binary
